<HEADLINE> Mango Export Earns Pakistan 689 Mln U.S. Dollars in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan exported 34,185 tons of
mangoes to Arabian, European and Asian countries and earned 689
million U.S. dollars during 1999, according to the Associated
Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
APP quoted sources at the Export Promotion Bureau (EPB) as
saying on Saturday the demand of Pakistani mangoes which are
considered best in the world is increasing which will help the
country to earn more foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
A two-day Millennium Mango and Summer Fruits Expo-2000 started
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The EPB sources said the main objective of arranging the
exhibition is to introduce best quality mangoes produced in
different parts of the country with over 50 mango varieties
including Dosehri, Anwar Rathe, Kala Chonsa, Samar Bahishat Chonsa,
Langra, Malda, Faiz Kareem, Sindhri, White Chonsa, Fajri,
Sanglakhi, Tamuria, Banarsi Langra, Hus Ara, Began Pali, and Late
Summer Chonsa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
