<HEADLINE> 7 People Killed in Police-Guerrillas Clash in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and
nine others injured Friday night when some 300 guerrillas launched
a bomb-attack at a police post in Sindhupalchowk district of
central Nepal, the official RSS news agency said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The killed include four policemen and three guerrillas while
five of the injured are in serious conditions, a police officer
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The police post has been completely destroyed and the
guerrillas managed to escape during a cross-fire between the two
sides, said the unidentified police officer.
</P>
<P>
At least 1,300 people, including policemen, guerrillas and
civilians, have been killed since the guerrillas began its armed
activities in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
