<HEADLINE> Botero Takes 14th Stage of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Santiago Botero scored Colombia's
first Tour de France stage win for four years when he took the 249.
5-km 14th stage on Saturday in Briancon, France.
</P>
<P>
He arrived two minutes 29 seconds ahead of Italian Paolo
Savoldelli in second place. Another Italian Marco Pantani
finished third.
</P>
<P>
American Lance Armstrong retained the overall lead. 
</P>
