<HEADLINE> France Ready to Cancel All Zambia's Due Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The French government has announced
that it is ready to cancel all the due debt Zambia owes it.
</P>
<P>
In celebration of the French National Day here on Friday,
French Ambassador to Zambia Jean-Louis Zoel said that both trade
and aid related debt will be written off and channeled into
development fund.
</P>
<P>
Zambia owes France a due debt of 130 million U.S. dollars.
