<HEADLINE> S. African Ruling Party Set to Recruit Minorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The ruling African National
Congress (ANC) Saturday called for a massive recruitment drive to
draw the country's minority whites, coloreds and Indians into its
fold.
</P>
<P>
Delegates who attended the party's five-day national general
council in Port Elizabeth this week, debated, among other things,
ways to eradicate racism and build a united South Africa.
</P>
<P>
They resolved that the ANC's highest decision-making body
between national conferences, the national executive committee,
should develop a strategy to draw colored, Indians and whites into
the party.
</P>
<P>
"We must combat any form of ethnicity, narrow nationalism and
regionalism within our ranks," a council report said.
</P>
<P>
The delegates also urged the ANC Youth League to "continue to
reach out to the white youth, especially Afrikaner youth and
identify a common platform for youth mobilization and organization.
"
</P>
<P>
ANC national chairman Mosiuoa Lekota told reporters on Saturday
that "we recognize it is our responsibility to create a climate,
both inside and outside the ANC, which will make it conducive for
a greater number of white South Africans, to move not just closer
to the ANC, but into the ANC."
</P>
<P>
The ANC recognized that it has to set up its structures in, for
example, white suburbs, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that if any section of the population wants to impact
decisively on the government policy, "they will not be able to do
that in some minority weak formations."
</P>
<P>
He was apparently referring to the new Democratic Alliance,
comprising the Democratic Party and the New National Party.
</P>
<P>
By joining the majority of black South Africans in the ANC,
whites and other minorities "can make effective contribution,
along side this majority, in shaping the direction this country
must take," Lekota said.
</P>
<P>
"The ANC is an instrument available to all sections of the
population of this country and we need to make it possible for
them to use the ANC to contribute to the transformation and the
building of the new South Africa," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
