- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian students on Sunday staged a "political fast"
before the office building of the Majlis (parliament) to protest
against the court verdict on last year's student dormitory case and
the imprisonment of a reformist lawyer.
</P>
<P>
The fast, held by Iran's most influential student organization,
the Office to Foster Unity (OFU), may continue in the next few days
to urge the Majlis to take quick measures to overhaul the
conservative judiciary, said a statement released by OFU. (Iran-
Fast)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli defense establishment has reacted with
concern to Iran's successful test-firing of an upgraded version of
its medium-range Shahab-3 missile on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Israel believes Iran will have a small number of nuclear
warheads which will be operational in about five years, he added.
The launching of the missile Saturday was not seen as a surprise to
Israel which has been following its development. (Israel-Iran-
Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
Tel Aviv -- Hundreds of thousands of Israeli right-wing
protestors rallied Sunday evening at Rabin Square in the center of
Tel Aviv to protest against the ongoing Camp David summit.
</P>
<P>
Organized by various settler's organizations and the opposition
Likud Party, the protestors also expressed their opposition to the
government's intention to withdraw from large areas of the
territories and dismantle some Jewish settlements in the
territories. (Israel-Rally) 
</P>
