<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Rowers Get Life Ban for Test Failure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUCERNE, Switzerland, July 16 (Xinhua) -- FISA has imposed life
bans on three rowers who have tested positive for anabolic
steroids, the international rowing federation announced here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Giovany Solo Lopez of tested positive for metabolites of
nandrolone in an out-of-competition test at a training camp in
Mexico City. He was a member of the Cuban men's quadruple scull
which had already qualified for the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Natalia Lavrenenko and Natalia Stasiok, members of the Belarus
women's quadruple scull, were tested at a training center in
Belarus.Lavrenenko tested positive for metabolites of epimetendiol.
Stasiok tested positive for metabolites of methyltestosterone.
</P>
<P>
The rules of FISA impose a life ban for a first offense in the
case of a positive test for anabolic steroids. Accordingly, the
three rowers named above are now banned for life from competitive
rowing.
</P>
<P>
FISA is one of the leading international federations in the
fight against doping and was the first federation to introduce out-
of-competition testing in 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
