<HEADLINE> Dalian Shide Keep Winning Streak in Chinese First Division League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Substitute Hu Zhaojun scored the
winner in injury time to give Dalian Shide a 2-1 victory over
Shenyang Haishi in the 18th round of the Chinese first division
soccer league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Dalian Shide retain a 7-point advantage over
Shanghai Shenhua and Shandong Luneng, which beat their respective
rivals on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian team conceded a goal in the first half, but that
never worried them. Only three minutes into the second half, Li
Ming slamed home from close range to level the score at 1-1.
</P>
<P>
The winner came in injury time when Hu Zhaojun's shot from 30
meters changed direction after hitting a defender bounced into the
net.
</P>
<P>
It was Dalian's 13th victory this season. Now they have
garnered 42 points with eight round of competitions remaining this
season.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua and Shandong Luneng, the other two teams had
ever won the league title since China launched professional soccer
league in 1994, stayed in the three-way race as they both beat
their rivals.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Shenhua beat Liaoning Fushun 1-0 while Shandong Luneng
trounced Qingdao Hainiu 4-2.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Luneng and Shanghai Shenhua each have 35 points, 7
points behind Leaders Dalian Shide but still have the chance to
win the league title.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's other matches, Yunnan Hongta tied with Beijing Guo
'an 0-0, Shenzhen Ping'an beat Jilin Aodong 3-0, Xiamen Xiaxin
forced Tianjin Taida to a 2-2 draw while Chongqing Longxin downed
Sichuan Quanxin 2-1. 
</P>
