<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Irian Jaya, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on the
Richter Scale jolted Indonesia's Irian Jaya province on Sunday
night.
</P>
<P>
The Antara News Agency quoted Geophysics and Meteorology Body
as saying that the quake occurred at 20:38 p.m. local time (11:38
GMT).
</P>
<P>
The quake centered 4.39 degrees southern latitude and 139.54
degrees eastern longitude, about 100 kilometers southeastern of
Wamena city.
</P>
<P>
Antara reported that an aftershock, also measuring 5.2 on the
Richter Scale, hit the same area half an hour later.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damages.
</P>
</TEXT>
