<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Military Delegation Visits Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A high-level Vietnamese military
delegation has paid an official goodwill visit to Laos, discussing
measures to promote mutual assistance and cooperation between the
two armies of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The six-day visit, led by Vietnam's Deputy Defense Minister
Lieutenant General Le Van Dung, member of the Communist Party of
Vietnam Central Committee and Chief of the General Staff of the
Vietnam People's Army, wrapped up on Sunday, according to a report
of Vietnam's official news agency VNA Sunday.
</P>
<P>
While in Laos, the Vietnamese military officials held talks
with their Lao counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The two sides informed each other of the achievements in
national and army construction as well as the domestic, regional
and international situation.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed activities to promote mutual assistance and
set the orientation for further friendship and cooperation in the
near future.
</P>
<P>
The delegation was received by Lao Prime Minister Sisavath
Keobounphanh who expressed high appreciation of the results of the
delegation's visit, saying it contributed to the special
solidarity and friendship between the two parties, states and
armies.
</P>
<P>
They paid a courtesy visit to Lao Deputy Prime Minister and
Defense Minister Chummaly Saynhason.
</P>
<P>
The visit was made at the invitation of Douangchay Phichith,
member of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party Central Committee
and Chief of the General Staff of the Lao People's Army.  
</P>
</TEXT>
