<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Marine Products Export Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam earned 512 million U.S.
dollars from marine products exports in the first half of this
year, a year-on-year increase of 24.7 percent, Vietnam News Agency
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the output of for-export marine
products of the country reached 950,000 tonnes, a year-on-year
rise of 7.7 percent, with 316,000 tonnes from aquaculture and the
rest from fishing.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's fisheries sector has constantly invested in
infrastructural facilities such as fishing harbors and vessels
using capital from various sources.
</P>
<P>
The sector has better coordinated with localities to raise its
annual output to 720,000 tonnes in 2000 from 614,500 tonnes last
year. As many as 2,125 shrimp farms nationwide turned out 4.5
billion baby shrimp and 340 fishing farms, 6.5 billion young fish,
meeting almost all the requirements of breeders for fry.
</P>
<P>
The country now counts 57 shrimp and fish food producers, who
turn out 50,000 tonnes of high-quality products annually. Shrimp
is now a key item in aquaculture development.
</P>
<P>
The fisheries sector of the country plans to earn 1.1 billion U.
S.dollars from exports this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
