<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethnic Clothing, Decoration Exposition Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A 14-day exposition showing unique
and valuable costumes from China's 56 ethnic minority groups
closed today in this capital of southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Lei Xiaoming, deputy mayor of Kunming, said that the exposition
is expected to exert long-time influence on folk costume
development. Over 3,405 costumes and 15,000 ornaments from 20
ethnic minority areas were on display.
</P>
<P>
Some 600 models from 24 provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions participated in a modeling contest, and 590
designers attended a fashion contest during the period.
</P>
<P>
Also, 100 scholars gathered during the activity to discuss how
to intensify the combination of folk costumes with fashion, and to
accelerate sales of folk costumes both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The exposition won four Guinness records -- for being the first
one of its kind in China, and for holding the first folk costume
design contest and the first folk costume modeling contest.
</P>
<P>
Giant-sized folk costumes were displayed at the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Exposition of Ethnic Clothing and Decorations, co-hosted by
the State Ethnic Affairs Commission and the Yunnan provincial
government, was the first of its kind ever held in China, which is
home to 56 nationalities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000716.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Official Warns of Drought And Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
warned here today that drought and floods might hit China at the
same time, as the weather in the near future is unpredictable.
</P>
<P>
Visiting some key reservoirs in this north China port city, Wen
said that the country is experiencing serious droughts, which are
getting worse in some northern provinces.
</P>
<P>
At the meantime, he said, the flood season has arrived, and
flood prevention work should be intensified.
</P>
<P>
Previous reports said that rainstorms have killed dozens of
people in the southwest part of the country. Some one million
people have been mobilized along the Yellow River to prepare
against possible floods.
</P>
<P>
Wen also said that the shortage of water will be a long-term
factor hindering the country's economic development. To solve the
problem, people should have a better awareness of the importance
of saving water.
</P>
<P>
He added that water should be saved not only in the countryside,
but also in the cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
