<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Wins Austrian Formula One Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Mika Hakkinen of Finland drove his
McLaren-Mercedes to take the title of the Austrian Grand Prix at
Spielberg, Austria, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hakkinen, who started from the pole position, led from start to
finish to beat fellow McLaren-Mercedes driver David Coulthard. It
is McLaren-Mercedes second 1-2 finish in a row and fourth of the
season.
</P>
<P>
Rubens Barrichello was third in a Ferrari and former world
champion Jacques Villeneuve of Canada finished fourth in a BAR-
Honda.
</P>
<P>
Michael Schumacher of Ferrari was bumped by Ricardo Zonta's BAR-
Honda in the first corner after the start and as he spun across
the track, he was rammed by the Jordan of Jarno Trulli.
</P>
<P>
The incident took both Schumacher and Trulli out of the race.
</P>
<P>
It was the third time in the last four races that Schumacher
failed to finish.
</P>
<P>
With seven Grand Prix left in the 17-race season, three drivers
now have a shot at the title.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher still tops the standings with 56 points, Coulthard
has 50 and Hakkinen 48. 
