<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Urges Improved National Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
here Saturday that the country should improve its national defense
while developing its economy.
</P>
<P>
Visiting a defense industry exhibition, Zhu urged that a
vigorous system be created to develop military science, and
nationwide cooperation be expanded in this regard by adhering to
the principle of self-reliance.
</P>
<P>
The premier stressed that the defense industry should be
combined with the civilian sector, and their cooperation should be
market-oriented.
</P>
<P>
He noted that many military plants are suffering losses due to
the dogma of the planned economy.
</P>
<P>
The defense industry should develop technologies and products
that can be accepted by both military and civilian markets, he
said, adding that different research institutes and sectors should
combine their strengths.
</P>
<P>
In addition, those civilian enterprises that produce military
products should take this mission as their priority, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing also visited the exhibition on the
cooperative results achieved in the defense industry. 
</P>
