<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Two people, including a boy, were
killed and 33 others wounded when a powerful bomb exploded Sunday
morning in Kabacan, North Cotabato Province, in the southern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded in a public market in the town of Kabacan as
market goers milled around stalls, according to local press
reports.
</P>
<P>
Those wounded were rushed to various hospitals in the area for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
Town mayor Wilfredo Bataga blamed the Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF) for the bombing, citing an order of its leader Hashim
Salamat to launch a "Jihad" or holy war against their enemies
after the MILF headquarters Abubakar fell to government troops
last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But MILF spokesman Eid Kabalu denied that the group was behind
the incident.
</P>
<P>
In April, a bomb exploded inside a department store in Kabacan,
killing three people. 
