<HEADLINE> Five Killed, Several Injured in Ship Collision in Gibraltar Strait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Two ferries collided near the
Gibraltar Strait Sunday morning, killing at least five people,
including two children, and injuring several others.
</P>
<P>
The two ships collided head-on with each other near the
southern Spanish port of Algeciras, where some 300 passengers on
board of the ferries are now staying.
</P>
<P>
Spanish port officials attributed the accident to poor
visibility in the strait, but no definite conclusion has been made.
</P>
