<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government said
Sunday that at least 14 Tamil Tiger rebels had been killed in
fresh sporadic fighting which erupted between government troops
and the rebels in the north of the island while foreign guests are
visiting the country to assess the peace prospects.
</P>
<P>
The government said in a statement that troops killed 11 rebels
of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) on Saturday in three
clashes in the northern Jaffna peninsula, the scene of weeks of
fierce fighting until May.
</P>
<P>
It added that three LTTE rebels were killed on Friday also in
the Jaffna peninsula.
</P>
<P>
