presented by the Leisure and Cultural Services Department (LCSD)
and will be held from July 16 to September 17 at the Hong Kong
International Airport Passenger Terminal Building.
</P>
<P>
"Lantern Exhibition and Cultural Performances at the Airport"
comprises a series of mid-autumn lantern displays and traditional
Chinese cultural performances.
</P>
<P>
The lantern exhibition is aimed at promoting traditional
Chinese culture and customs among tourists and local community as
well as serving as a prelude to the annual Mid-autumn Lantern
Carnivals to be held in September.
</P>
<P>
The six groups of thematic lanterns are "Lotus Pond and Full
Moon", "Chinese Theater", "Story of Mid-Autumn Festival", "The
Moon Lady", "Animal Land" and "Insect World". 
</P>
</TEXT>
