<HEADLINE> 3 Rowers Banned for Life for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Three rowers have been banned for
life after testing positive for anabolic steroids, the
International Rowing Federation (FISA) announced in Lucerne on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
They were named as women rowers Natalia Lavrenenko and Natalia
Stasiok, who are members of the Belarus quadruple scull team, and
men rower Giovany Solo Lopez of Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Lopez tested positive for metabolites of nandrolone in an out-
of-competition test at a training camp in Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
Lavrenenko and Stasiok were tested at a training center in
Belarus. Lavrenenko tested positive for metabolites of
epimetendiol. Stasiok tested positive for metabolites of
methyltestosterone. 
</P>
