<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Will Never Yield to U.S. Domination: Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin
has said Iraq will never kneel down to the domination of the United
States, condemning the U.S. domination in the U.N. Security
Council.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has utilized the U.N. Security Council to struggle
against the Third World states, especially those rejecting the U.S.
subordination and submission, Ramadan said, quoted Sunday by the
official daily Al-Jumhuriya.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the decade-old sanctions against Iraq will never be
lifted by a U.N. Security Council resolution, said Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
Ramadan criticized the Arab League (AL) for failing to play its
role to alleviate the sufferings of the Iraqi people, who have been
the hardest hit by the sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Ramadan also urged the Arab and Muslim countries to take action
to break the "unjust" sanctions on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has repeatedly protested to the U.N. and the AL against the
continued U.S. and British aggressions over the two no-fly zones in
northern and southern Iraq, and demanded them to pressure the U.S.
and Britain to stop such aggressive acts, but so far has received
little response.
</P>
<P>
The no-fly zones were imposed on Iraq by the U.S.-led Western
allies following the 1991 Gulf War, with the claimed aim of
protecting the Kurds in the north and Shiite Muslims in the south
against possible attacks by Iraqi government troops.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has never recognized the zones for lack of explicit U.N.
authorization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
