<HEADLINE> Automatic Cash-Paying Machine Service to Be Available in Ethiopia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian bank depositors are
expected to withdrawal money from machines without the involvement
of bankers, Ethiopian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned Commercial Bank of Ethiopia (CBE) will begin
providing the new services in the coming Ethiopian year that
begins on September 12.
</P>
<P>
By that time, customers could withdraw money by simply
inserting cards and entering pass words into the machines, CBE
Loan and Administration Deputy President Hailu Legesse was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The technology will enable the CBE to promote its services to
an international standard, Hailu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
