<HEADLINE> South Africa to Bid for 2010 World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- South African soccer
officials will ask world ruling body FIFA for the right to host
the 2010 World Cup after losing the bid for the 2006 tournament,
according to an AFP report.
</P>
<P>
Bid committee chief executive Danny Jordaan told AFP that they
would also support calls for the event to be rotated by continent
and challenge the composition of FIFA's executive, a third of whom
are from Europe, but had not yet decided whether to call for a
revote for the 2006 event.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's July 6 vote for the host of the 2006 World Cup became
controversial after Oceania representative Charles Dempsey
abstained, resulting in Germany winning the bid by 12 votes to
South Africa's 11. 
</P>
</TEXT>
