<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals to Cyprus Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- June 2000 saw the number of
tourists to Cyprus reaching 306,049, up 10.5 percent from the same
month last year, local newspaper Sunday Mail reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus government predicted that tourist arrivals will set a
record of more than 2.7 million for the whole year. In 1999, some
2.4 million holiday-makers visited the island.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists in the first six months of the year
topped the one million mark for the first time, with a rise of
12.6 percent compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
There was also a record growth in the number of American
tourists to Cyprus, up a massive 56 percent. Visitors from the
Britain
increased by 16 percent and those from Germany by 10.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The tourist industry is the largest sector in the island's
economy, providing more than 20 percent of GDP (gross domestic
product).  
</P>
</TEXT>
