<HEADLINE> 2 Hezbollah Men Killed in Fire Exchange With Amal in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Two militiamen of Hezbollah were
killed and at least one injured in fire exchange with another
militia organization Amal movement on Saturday night in south
Lebanon, Lebanese police said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred in the village of Malkaba in central
section of the former Israeli occupied zone, the police said but
did not revealed the cause of the conflict.
</P>
<P>
It was the first conflict between the two Shiite organizations,
which have fought against the Israeli occupation side by side,
since Israel withdrew its troops from south Lebanon on May 24,
</P>
<P>
After Israel's pullout, the two organizations control the
region. So far, the Lebanese government refuses to deploy its army
in
the south, claiming it will not be operated until the U.N. confirms

Israel's withdrawal and deploys its peacekeeping forces there
first.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, detached from Amal movement in 1982, spearheaded the
fighting against Israel's occupation in south Lebanon. Amal
movement is headed by Lebanese Parliament Speaker Nabih Berri.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
