<DOCNO> XIE20000716.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's New Missile Threatens Region: Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Israel has voiced its concern
over Iran's successful test-firing of an upgraded version of its
medium-range Shahab-3 missile, saying the new missile could pose a
threat not only to Israel, but to the region.
</P>
<P>
Iran test-launched on Saturday a Shahab-3 ballistic missile and
declared it a success. Israel said the 1,300-kilometer range
missile could reach targets across Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security officials said Saturday night that while the
test run does not pose an immediate threat to Israel's security, it
is clear that Iran is establishing its strategic capability.
</P>
<P>
"The successful test run is a worrying sign...this is a step
forward in the Iranian buildup of power," Deputy Defense Minister
Ephraim Sneh told the Army Radio.
</P>
<P>
"The strength of the Israel Defense Force and the strengthening
of Israel by peace agreements are together our answer to this
launch," Israel Radio quoted Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak as
reporting on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Barak is at Camp David, the United States, attending the three-
way summit with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and U.S, President
Bill Clinton to discuss how to settle the key issues, such as the
fate of Jerusalem, Jewish settlements, Palestinian refugees,
borders, in the Israeli-Palestinian final-status talks.
</P>
<P>
Officials with Barak at the Camp David said the new Iranian
Shahab-3 missile "is a signal not only to us but to the region as a
whole and it threatens the whole region and goes to show the need
to immediately stop financial aid to Iran," the radio added.
</P>
<P>
Shahab-3 is modelled mainly on North Korea's Nodong-1, but has
been improved with Russian technology. It is a single stage
ballistic missile, using liquid fuel and with a speed of about 7,
000 kilometers per hour. It can carry an 800-kilogram warhead.
</P>
<P>
In July 1998, Iran test-fired the Shahab-3 for the first time
but it exploded during the launch due to a system failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
