<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Launches Resettlement Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The resettling of the landless
Zimbabweans has started on 200 white commercial farms acquired by
the government throughout the country, the Sunday Mail reported.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here Saturday, Vice-President
Joseph Msika said this followed the amendment of the Constitution
and the subsequent amendment of the Land Acquisition Act under
which the government published a list of 804 white-owned farms for
acquisition.
</P>
<P>
"This legal framework has removed the impediments that has
hindered the government from quick acquisition of land for
resettlement," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the government had now adopted the "fast track"
approach that priority would be given to land acquisition,
demarcation, settler emplacement and the provision of basic
infrastructure such as water points and access roads.
</P>
<P>
He said the farms to be targeted would be the derelict ones,
those being underutilized, the ones belonging to absent landlords,
those adjacent to communal areas and those that were under
multiple ownership.
</P>
<P>
Beneficiary selection would be done in accordance with the
established resettlement and land redistribution policies and
procedures of the government.
</P>
<P>
He said the whole process was designed to ensure fair and
equitable redistribution of land so as to correct the racial
imbalance in land ownership created by former colonial regimes.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, leader of the Zimbabwean War Veterans Association
Chenjerai Hunzvi has given the government a two week ultimatum in
which it had to acquire all the 804 designated farms.
</P>
<P>
"I do not like to give ultimatums to the government, but if
they move slowly in acquiring the land within the next two weeks
then we will do it ourselves," he told war veterans in Harare
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The war veterans have occupied about 1,500 white farms since
February this year to press for acceleration of land
redistribution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
