<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, July 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Gunfights continued in Ambon, capital of Indonesia's
Maluku province, on Saturday, forcing residents to stay at home
for fear of being shot.
</P>
<P>
"Sounds of gunfire and grenade and bomb explosions have been
heard since 07:00 a.m. (local time). It is like a war in the
Middle East or something. Thick smoke is billowing out here and
there. We cannot see anything farther than 20 meters," The Jakarta
Post Sunday quoted a reporter based in Ambon as saying.
</P>
<P>
The reporter said no one dared to go out, "therefore there is
no way for us to find out how many more people have been killed
and how many buildings were ravaged or burned down on Saturday."
(Indonesia-Violence)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton held a trilateral
meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat from Friday night to early Saturday morning,
the second of its kind since the summit began at Camp David on
July 11.
</P>
<P>
A White House official, speaking on condition of anonymity,
said that the meeting lasted 90 minutes until around 1 a.m. EDT (
0500 GMT) Saturday after Barak hosted U.S. and Palestinian
delegations at a traditional Jewish Sabbath dinner at the U.S.
presidential retreat on Friday night. The three leaders were
joined only by interpreters and note-takers and details of the
meeting were not released in line with the total news blackout
imposed during the summit. (Clinton-Barak-Arafat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia, a country straddling the Eurasian continent,
should seek a balanced development in its foreign policy, Russian
President Vladimir Putin said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"The main task of the Russian foreign policy is to maintain a
balance between the world's forces and interests," Putin said in
an interview with Xinhua News Agency and China Central Television
on the eve of his visit to China which starts Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that top priorities should be given to settling
domestic problems. "A country cannot play an effective role on the
international arena without adequately settling domestic problems,
" he said. (Russia-Putin-Foreign Policy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- At least 10 people were killed and 30 others were
injured on Sunday morning when a bomb exploded at a passenger
train near the southern Pakistani city of Hyderabad.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred at about 7:00 a.m. (0200 GMT) in the last
carriage of the Mehran Express train shortly after it left the
Hyderabad railway station on a regular trip to the port city of
Karachi. Witnesses said the huge bang emitted a big cloud of fume
and people panicked ran for shelter. Four people were died on the
spot while six others demised in a local hospital. Among the dead
were three women and four children. (Pakistan-Blast-Toll) 
