<HEADLINE> Eastern China City Cracks Down on Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers in Xiamen, the
main port city in east China's Fujian Province, have stricken out
at smugglers this year.
</P>
<P>
Between January and June, Xiamen customs cracked 119 smuggling
cases involving 648.7 million yuan (about 78 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The number of cases during the period decreased 53 percent from
the same period last year, but the money involved increased by 143
percent, statistics indicated.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities have vowed to increase offshore patrols and
tighten inspections on vessels in key sea areas, distributing
centers and ports to plug loopholes. Intelligence agents will also
be deployed in the anti-smuggling campaign. 
</P>
</TEXT>
