Palestinian negotiations at Camp David, U.S. President Bill Clinton
managed to dissuade Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat from leaving
the summit.
</P>
<P>
Arafat threatened to leave after U.S. Middle East special envoy
Dennis Ross submitted a suggestion on the status of Jerusalem on
Thursday night, which the Palestinians claimed was too similar to
the Israeli position.
</P>
<P>
President Clinton met both leaders on Friday and the Israeli
delegation invited the Palestinians and American delegations to a
Shabbat dinner. The three leaders then met alone until 1 a.m..
There were no official meetings on Saturday morning.
</P>
