minor summit crisis at Camp David on Friday morning when Arafat
demanded that a group of three Palestinians, not originally part of
his delegation, be allowed to consult the Palestinians already
there.
</P>
<P>
Albright met with the group near Camp David and explained why
they could not join the Palestinian delegation. She also promised
to raise the matter with President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The three are Fatah members -- heads of factions who supported
Arafat going to the summit and who are influential in Palestinian
domestic politics. Arafat wanted to include them to broaden his
circle of support.
