<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 16 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed
and 30 others were injured on Sunday morning when a bomb exploded
at a passenger train near the southern Pakistani city of Hyderabad,
informed sources told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred at about 7:00 a.m. (0200 GMT) in the last
carriage of the Mehran Express train shortly after it left the
Hyderabad railway station on a regular trip to the port city of
Karachi, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the huge bang emitted a big cloud of fume and
people panicked ran for shelter.
</P>
<P>
Four people were died on the spot while six others demised in a
local hospital. Among the dead were three women and four children.
</P>
<P>
Local officials feared death toll might continue to rise as
some of the injured were in critical conditions.
</P>
<P>
No one has so far claimed responsibility of the blast. 
