<HEADLINE> New Generation Red-Flag Car Rolls Off Production Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A new generation Red Flag car,
dubbed the "star of the century," rolled off the production line
Saturday at the First Automobile Works (FAW) Group based in
Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The Red Flag vehicle was developed by FAW Group to greet the
competition emerging from China's expected entry into the World
Trade Organization, and is also the only design for which China
possesses full intellectual property rights.
</P>
<P>
An FAW engineer said the car combines safety, economy, comfort
and environment-friendly features and has a sleeker, more modern
frame.
</P>
<P>
The first Red Flag car was produced by the First Automobile
Factory in 1958.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Fangkuan, general manager of FAW Sedan Cars Co., Ltd.,
said more new-generation Red Flag cars would be produced and put
out in the market soon.
</P>
<P>
