<HEADLINE> Inflation Falls Below 6 Percent in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is the first time in nine weeks that the country's
inflation level has gone below six percent.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous week, the inflation rate during the
week ended July 1 fell by 0.28 percentage points, said the release,
adding that the rate for the corresponding week last year was only
1.91 percent.
</P>
<P>
Inflation has been moving down in the past few weeks mainly on
account of a decline in agricultural prices, it noted.
</P>
