suspension following an air-crash in central China.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese-made Yun-7 passenger plane of the Wuhan Airlines
departed from Enshi City to Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province, on
June 22 and crashed shortly before arrival, killing all four crew
members and 38 passengers aboard.
</P>
<P>
