<HEADLINE> 111 Bridges Built in Myanmar in 12 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has built a total of 111
bridges in the country since 1988, spending 108.826 million U.S.
dollars plus 305.25 billion Kyats (872 million dollars), official
newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Myanmar Ministry of Construction has also built 6,
916.8 kilometers of roads since 1988 with its total length
extended to 30,232.8 km.
</P>
<P>
