<HEADLINE> Brunei's Ruler Stresses Importance of Regional Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SERI BEGAWAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Brunei's Sultan Hassanal
Bolkiah said Saturday that regional peace and security are some of
the preconditions that will allow his country and people to
continue enjoying prosperity and national building.
</P>
<P>
Bolkiah, who also holds the positions of prime minister and
minister of defense, made the remarks at his 54th birthday party
held at the royal palace here. In Brunei, which is rich with oil
and populated by 330,000 people, the sultan's birthday serves as a
grand festival nationwide every year.
</P>
<P>
In such a world that is currently experiencing changes and
formidable challenges brought about by the new millennium, Bolkiah
said, the reason why Brunei still enjoys peace, prosperity and
development is diligence and cooperation of both the private and
public sectors and citizens and inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
Bolkiah promised that Brunei Darussalam will continue to uphold
the principles of cooperation with friendly countries.
</P>
<P>
"This concept will be employed in our interaction with APEC,
ASEAN, the United Nations, the Commonwealth and other
international bodies and regional organizations," the ruler of
Brunei said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Brunei will make good use of its involvement as
the host of this year's APEC 2000 and the Visit Brunei Year 2001.
</P>
<P>
The informal summit of the Asian-Pacific Economic Cooperation (
APEC) will be held in November in Seri Begawan, capital of Brunei.
</P>
<P>
