<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINJIANG: Customs officials in Urumqi, capital of northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, recently seized 170 kg
of cashmere smuggled from Mongolia. The aim of the move is to cut
off the inflow of animal by-products from the areas plagued by the
hoof-and-mouth disease in neighboring Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
People in Xinjiang will be able to view the entire course of a
eclipse of the moon on July 16. Experts from the Urumqi
Astronomical Station under the Chinese Academy of Sciences said
that the lunar eclipse will begin at 7:57 p.m. (Beijing Time) and
end at 11:54 pm (Beijing Time).
</P>
<P>
JIANGSU: The Intermediate People's Court in Nanjing, capital of
east China's Jiangsu Province, granted on July 14 death penalty to
all four jobless youths who are convicted of murdering and robbing
a German family of four. At midnight on April 1, the four accused
broke into the Nanjing residence of the Pfrang family and stabbed
to death all the family members.
</P>
<P>
ZHEJIANG: China has released 1.1 million fry of large yellow
croakers into the East China Sea this year to help increase their
numbers. About 300,000 fry have been sent to the Zhoushan sea area,
China's largest fishing ground, off Zhejiang. The rest went to
nearby Xiangshan Bay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
