<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING: China will shut down 800 enterprises in the Three
Gorges areas in three years, which are losing money and producing
heavy pollution. A total of 1,500 enterprises in the Three Gorges
Dam area are to be relocated to make way for the construction of
the dam, with more than one million people to be resettled.
</P>
<P>
LIAONING: China's first robot development and production
company was set up on July 10 in Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province. The establishment of the Siasun Robot &AMP;
Automation Co., Ltd. signifies the start of market-oriented
industrial robot production in China.
</P>
<P>
NINGXIA: The desert in Shapotou, Zhongwei County, in northwest
China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, has become a major tourist
attraction in recent years. The desert, a natural reserve, is best
known for the Baotou-Lanzhou railway running through it and for
sand hills said to produce unusual sounds.
</P>
<P>
GANSU: China will invest 800 million yuan to build a new
tourism zone in Dunhuang, a city renowned for the Buddhist art of
the Mogao Grottos in northwest China's Gansu Province. The new
zone will be located at the Yitang Lake, 20 kilometers east of
downtown Dunhuang and 15 kilometers from the Mogao Grottos, which
were added to the World Heritage List in 1987.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
