<DOCNO> XIE20000716.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's first airport built with investments from farmers was
recently put into operation in Pinggu County of Beijing. The
Rongdong Airport was built with a total investment of 3.5 million
yuan from 700 households in Heidouyu Village of Pinggu.
</P>
<P>
Beijing is determined to become the country's top software
development and production base in three years, taking advantage
of its strong advantages in technologies and talents that are
essential for developing the software industry, according to Vice-
Mayor Lin Wenyi.
</P>
<P>
China's first pop music odeum made its debut in Beijing
recently. Pop music soirees will be held at the odeum every Friday
evening. New songs as well as new singers will be introduced to
the audience while classic pop songs will be reviewed.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 6.0 on the Richter scale hit Hualien
County of Taiwan at 8:07 Beijing time on July 14, according to the
China Seismological Bureau in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
SHANGHAI: A two-month exhibition on contemporary world
astronautic science, technology, and culture opened in Shanghai on
July 9. The mysterious spaceship Discovery, Apollo Moon Cabin,
China's Long March 4 carrier rocket and some other famous space
navigation tools are available on the show.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
