<DOCNO> XIE20000716.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Regional News In China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING: A forum on micronutrient fortification in China was
held here on July 10, in a bid to push forward food micronutrient
fortification in the country. Micronutrient deficiency in food is
a major health problem facing developing countries, and food
fortification is a useful means to solve it.
</P>
<P>
Four major Chinese airlines and four airports were voted as
having outstanding service in a recent poll of more than 50,000
passengers. Air China, Hainan Airlines, Xiamen Airlines and
Shenzhen Airlines are selected as the four top airlines. Shanghai
Hongqiao Airport was voted top of its division of more than eight
million passengers per year.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-seven out of the approximately 15,000 registered
websites in China have been chosen to pilot on-line advertising,
according to the State Administration for Industry and Commerce.
The lucky websites, including www.sohu.com, www.netease.net and
etang.com, are selected for being "well-established" and all of
them are registered in Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Beijing reported on July 12 a maximum temperature of 40 degrees
Celsius (104 Fahrenheit). This is the second time that the capital
city was hit by a heat wave since July 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
