<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Bulgarians Killed in Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Three persons have been killed and
an unknown number of people injured in fires in Bulgaria by
Saturday evening since fires caused by high temperature erupted in
many Bulgarian areas in June.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian news agency BTA reported that two of the three
dead were found accidentally in a scorched field in eastern
Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
No official figure of injured persons was reported, but in
Dimitrovgrad alone, eastern Bulgaria, 30 adults and 25 children
were sent to hospitals after they were burnt by fires.
</P>
<P>
A crisis center was set up in July to report fire disasters to
the authorities every one hour.
</P>
<P>
Eight fires are still raging in southern Bulgaria and 27,000
hectares of forests have been destroyed in the whole country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
