<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Seized 39.56 kgs of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Customs officers Saturday
seized 39.56 kilograms of heroin at the Andreevo border checkpoint
on a coach from Turkey, reported the Bulgarian Telegraph Agency (
BTA).
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 775.56 kilograms of heroin have been seized
at the checkpoint, hitting an all-time high in Europe, said the
BTA.
</P>
<P>
Of the three drivers, two are Turkish and the other is a
Macedonian. They hid 76 packages of heroin in the two-deck
metallic roof in an attempt to smuggle them into Albania via
Bulgaria and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The BTA said the coach has been confiscated and that the three
drivers detained according to the Bulgarian law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
