<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Seeks Balanced Foreign Policy, Says Putin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia, a country straddling the
Eurasian continent, should seek a balanced development in its
foreign policy, Russian President Vladimir Putin said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"The main task of the Russian foreign policy is to maintain a
balance between the world's forces and interests," Putin said in
an exclusive interview with the Xinhua News Agency and the China
Central Television on the eve of his visit to China which starts
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that top priorities should be given to settling
domestic problems. "A country cannot play an effective role on
the international arena without adequately settling domestic
problems," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the interview, the Russian president also admitted that his
wife felt unhappy and wept for a whole day when she learnt he was
appointed acting president on the New Year's Eve following the
surprise resignation of Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Putin disclosed that he had to spend less time with his two
daughters at present. "When I leave home for office, they are
still asleep; and when I come back, they have already gone to bed.
"
</P>
<P>
Putin, 47, was officially sworn in as the new head of state
last May after winning the presidential campaign in March.
</P>
<P>
Putin is to pay a state visit to China from July 17 to 19.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
