<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Embarks on Five-Nation Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
left here today for an official visit to Myanmar, Thailand,
Indonesia, Belarus, and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Hu is paying the visit at the invitation of Vice-Chairman
General Maung Aye of the State Peace and Development Council of
Myanmar, the government of Thailand, Vice-President Megawati
Soekarno Putri of Indonesia, President Alexander Grigorievich
Lukashenko of Belarus, and President Nursultan Abishevich
Nazarbayev of Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Hu's entourage includes his wife Liu Yongqing, Deputy Foreign
Minister Wang Guangya, Deputy Director Ling Jihua of the General
Office of the Communist Party of China Central Committee, and
other senior government officials. 
</P>
