<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Education News in China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese Students Win Gold Medals at Int'l Chemistry Olympiad
</P>
<P>
Four Chinese middle school students won three gold medals and
one silver at the 32nd International Chemistry Olympiad, which
ended Monday in Copenhagen, Denmark.
</P>
<P>
The gold medal winners were Chen Zheng from Hunan Province,
Feng Wei from Hubei Province and Tang Yanwei from Zhejiang
Province. Zhang Jing from Jiangsu Province won the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
A total of 208 students from 54 countries and regions
participated in the contest.
</P>
<P>
Int'l Conference on Tele-Education Opens in Beijing
</P>
<P>
The 7th annual conference of the International Education and
Resource Network opened on July 11 in Beijing, drawing more than
400 education experts, teachers and students from 60 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
The seven-day conference will exhibit the world's most
successful tele-education models and promote education through the
Internet, especially in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
