<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, July 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South African President Thabo Mbeki Saturday
declared war on corrupt officials who are using state resources
that are supposed to go to communities for their own ends.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a rally in Zwide township in Port Elizabeth, Mbeki
urged communities to reject the names of any corrupt candidate
nominated to stand for the local elections.  (SAfrica-
Corruption)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HAVANA -- Some 20,000 Cuban demonstrators Saturday demanded the
derogation by the United States of a law that grants automatic
asylum to Cubans who abandon the island.
</P>
<P>
Revolutionary Armed Forces Minister and No. 2 leader in Cuba
Raul Castro attended the rally held in La Maquina, 900 kilometers
east of Havana.
</P>
<P>
"Down with the Cuban Adjustment Act" and "Down with the
blockade" were some of the slogans shouted by the demonstrators.
(Cuba-US-Adjustment Act)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan Saturday
warned Sierra Leonean rebels not to oppose the operation launched
by the U.N. mission to rescue peacekeepers who had been trapped by
them since May this year.
</P>
<P>
More than 220 U.N. peacekeepers trapped in eastern Sierra
Leone broke out from their positions with the help of fellow
peacekeepers from the United Nations Mission in Sierra Leone
Saturday morning and began fighting their way toward safety. (UN-S.
Leone)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- Around 100,000 children aged from six to 14 years work
in conditions of slavery as domestic servants in Peru, revealed a
report published by the Center of Social Studies and Publications
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The study, which bares the serious situation of Peruvian
childhood, said that the infants are forced to execute heavy tasks,
for extenuating working hours, without time limit, and are exposed
to many humiliations. (Peru-Children)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Vietnam has made progress in power industry with power
grid coverage reaching all provinces of the country.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's electricity grid now covers all provinces of the
country with the connection last month of the northern mountainous
province of Lai Chau, Vietnam's official news agency VNA reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has increased electricity production by almost 13
percent in the past 12 months, with production of nearly 13
billion kwh in the first six months of the year. (Vietnam-Power
Grid)  
</P>
</TEXT>
