<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean President Appoints New Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
Saturday evening announced a 19-member cabinet with new surprises
which saw 18 former ministers losing their posts.
</P>
<P>
In the previous government, there were 27 ministers.
</P>
<P>
According to Mugabe, the new cabinet naturally reflected his
government's new thrust and the need to trim the previous cabinet.
</P>
<P>
In the new cabinet, Moven Mahachi returned as Defense Minister;
John Nkomo, former Minister of Public Construction and National
Housing, becomes the new Minister of Home Affairs; former Attorney-
General Patrick Chinamase becomes Minister of Justice, Legal and
Parliamentary Affairs; while Stan Mudenge retained his post as
Foreign Affairs Minister.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, former cabinet Minister and Executive Secretary of
the Southern African Development Community Simba Makoni becomes
new Minister of Finance and Economic Development, taking over from
Herbert Murerwa who is now Minister of Higher Education and
Technology.
</P>
<P>
In the President's Office, former Deputy Minister of Foreign
Affairs Nicholas Goche becomes Minister of State for National
Security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
