<HEADLINE> Mandela to Visit Burundi to Continue Peace Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Former South African
president Nelson Mandela will travel to Arusha, Tanzania next week
to facilitate the prepared text of a peace agreement, deal with
outstanding issues and engage with the Burundian leaders generally.
</P>
<P>
He would ensure that the parties recommit their previous pledge
to endorse the comprehensive peace agreement, according to a
statement by Mandela's office on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Mandela will also meet with and brief the Heads of States of
the Great Lakes Region and will inform them that the formal
adoption and signing of the peace agreement is to be scheduled for
August 28," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Mandela on Friday met with three other members of the peace
process facilitating team to asses the current state of progress
in the peace talks and to finalize the program for the talks
scheduled in Arusha.
</P>
<P>
The comprehensive peace plan would involve the 19 Burundian
parties participating in the process. 
</P>
