<HEADLINE> Two More Boats to Compete in 2000 Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUCERNE, Switzerland, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian men's
double sculls and the Canadian women's lightweight double sculls
have been allocated Olympic places and will race in the 2000
Olympic Games in Sydney, the international rowing federation FISA
announced here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The decision, made after consultation with the Sydney
Organizing Committee (SOCOG) and the International Olympic
Committee (IOC),follows the announcement by the Mexican National
Olympic Committee not to send its women's double sculls crew to
race in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
These additional qualifications bring the total number of boats
to race in Sydney to 197. 
</P>
