<HEADLINE> International Community Urged to Respect U.N. Sanctions Against UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano Monday appealed to the international community to abide
by the sanctions imposed by the United Nations Security Council
against the Angolan rebels led by Jonas Savimbi, reports reaching
here said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the third summit of the
Community of the Portuguese-speaking Countries (CPLP) in Maputo,
Chissano said the international community must continue "providing
humanitarian aid to the Angolan people, victim of the actions by
the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA)".
</P>
