<HEADLINE> S. African Delegation Leaves for Japan to Attend G8 Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A high-level South African
delegation left for Japan on Monday to attend the Group of Eight (
G8) Summit, the Foreign Affairs Department said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The summit of heads of state and government will be held on
July 21-23.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the presidents of South Africa, Algeria and
Nigeria have been mandated to represent the continent of Africa on
a variety of issues at the summit.
</P>
<P>
"It is expected ... that the African leaders will engage their
G8 counterparts on the cancellation of Africa's external debt, as
this continues to be an obstacle to, and has a negative effect on
development objectives," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of people-centered development and poverty
alleviation in Africa could be speeded up by the cancellation of
the unsustainable debt burden of developing countries, it said.
</P>
<P>
The G8 comprises Britain, Canada, France, Germany, Italy,
Japan, Russia and the United States. 
</P>
