<HEADLINE> East Timor to Join CPLP: Gusmao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- East Timor will join the Community
of the Portuguese-speaking Countries (CPLP) as its eighth member
once it gains full sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Xanana Gusmao, representative of the East Timorese delegation
and observer to the third summit of the CPLP, made the statement
at its opening session in Maputo on Monday, reports reaching here
said.
</P>
<P>
"East Timor will surely be the eighth member of the Community
of the Portuguese-speaking Countries", Gusmao said before
presenting the summit leaders with colorful Timorese "tais",
traditional hand-woven scarves.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, senior East Timorese diplomat Jose Ramos Horta
reaffirmed in Maputo the territory's choice of Portuguese as a
future "official language" alongside indigenous Tetum as its "
national language", adding that East Timor would also consider to
take English and Indonesia's Bahass Malay as working languages.
</P>
<P>
Residents in East Timor, a former Portuguese colony in
southeast Asia annexed in 1975 by Indonesia after the Portuguese
retreat, have voted in September 1999 for independence from
Jakarta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
