<HEADLINE> Nigerian President Invited to Attend OPEC Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Jorge Valero-Briceno, president of
the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), said
Monday in Nigeria's capital Abuja that OPEC was planning a summit
of heads of government of all its member states to find ways to
further strengthen the organization.
</P>
<P>
The visiting OPEC president said shortly after his meeting with
Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo that he had sent through the
invitation message to Obasanjo for the meeting scheduled for a
date between September 27 and 29 in Venezuelan capital Caracas.
</P>
<P>
The summit will be preluded by a session attended by ministers
of foreign affairs, finance, and petroleum from all its member
states, he said.
</P>
<P>
The OPEC president, who is also a special envoy of the
Venezuelan government, said the summit is part of the celebrations
marking the establishment of OPEC.
</P>
<P>
On the increasing price of crude oil on the world market
inspite of the injection of about 2.4 million barrel more oil per
day, Valero-Briceno said that the rising price was not the making
of the organization, which he said had taken all the necessary
measures to check the price. 
</P>
</TEXT>
